column6: NCALM - high rainfall, dense vegetation year

Does not contain Chichen, but includes surround area, data was collected between April 29 and May 03, 2017 as part of a lidar survey along the Yucatan Peninsula and San Gervasio, Mexico. This data was collected by NCALM for Travis Stanton in the Anthropology Department at University of California Riverside. Approximately 438 km2 of high resolution data were collected for this project.
Includes elcastillo, with some superstructure, no interior. Gran Juego Pelota, Templos Guerreros, Caracol, Monjas, and El Osario.
